  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"spell-description\">\n  <p>\n    <strong>School</strong>&nbsp;necromancy&nbsp;[disease, evil];\n    <strong>Level</strong>&nbsp;alchemist 6, antipaladin 6, cleric/oracle 6, druid 6, hunter 6, inquisitor 6, sorcerer/wizard 7, witch 6;\n    \n    \n    \n    \n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Casting Time</strong>&nbsp;1 standard action<br>\n    <strong>Components</strong>&nbsp;V, S<br>\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Range</strong>&nbsp;touch<br>\n    \n    <strong>Targets</strong>&nbsp;one living creature<br>\n    \n    <strong>Duration</strong>&nbsp;1 round/level; see text<br>\n    <strong>Saving Throw</strong>&nbsp;Fortitude negates; see text;&nbsp;<strong>Spell Resistance</strong>&nbsp;yes<br>\n  </p>\n  <h2>Description</h2>\n  <p>You make the target an asymptomatic carrier for a host of virulent diseases. Creatures that end their turn adjacent to the target must succeed at a Fortitude save or be affected as if by the spell <i>contagion</i>. The target itself does not become diseased, and suffers no ill effects from this spell. Once <i>plague bearer</i> ends, the target is no longer contagious, though any creature it infected remains diseased.</p>\n</div>\n",
